First:
  creating your app with: create-react-app hello -----> the example name
Second:
  creating your repository in github, example: hello
 Third:
  typing commands in your VScode like demonstrante in git to synchronize:
    . git init
    . git add
    . git commit
    . git remote
    . git push
 Fourth:
  installing via prompt command: npm i gh-pages
 Fifth:
  editing file packge.json and input that bellow:
    "homepage": "https://{YOUR GIT USER}.github.io/{YOUR REPOSITORY}/
    "prebuild": "npm run build"
    "deploy": "gh-pages -d build"
  Sixth:
    typing in your command prompt: npm run build
    when finished show the message: "Published"
    then copy the address and past on the browser
    
